latestPosts.caption:
Makeup for @themermaidscales for @graziaindia ‘s December 2024 Edition • @graziaindia #GraziaBeauty This year, beauty merged with AI in ways that truly reshaped the landscape. The fusion gave rise to a whole new aesthetic, and Y3K beauty entered the chat. Unlike Y2K, which celebrates early 2000s make-up, this has more of a futuristic style and visualises make-up looks in the year 3000. Even Pinterest’s Summer Trend Report of 2024 suggested that countless people were searching for the Y3K aesthetic. It represents elements of space and technology, and embraces silver metallics, rhinestones, avant-garde shapes, and glitter.

Words: Konika Datta 
Photograph: Yusuf Lokhandwala
Make-up: Saikat Chakraborty, National Artist, M.A.C Cosmetics India
Hair: Shimchuila Mungkung (Ashim) and Nikesh Sharma, Looks Salon

Makeup for @ankushbahuguna for @graziaindia ‘s December 2024 Edition • @graziaindia #GraziaBeauty Frosty make-up that incorporates cool and crisp tones of ice and snow was all the rage towards the end of this year, and rightfully so. This trend not only captures the season’s essence at its best, but it also adds a splash of dimension and glamour to our look, thanks to all the shimmer and shine. This look is typically a combination of icy lids, cold-bitten lips, and a natural-looking flush.

Words: Konika Datta 
Photograph: Yusuf Lokhandwala
Make-up: Saikat Chakraborty, National Artist, M.A.C Cosmetics India
Hair: Shimchuila Mungkung (Ashim) and Nikesh Sharma, Looks Salon
